25 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code ยง 6-60-214(a), concerning the eligibility
26 requirements for tuition benefits for soldiers and airmen of the Arkansas
27 National Guard, is amended to read as follows:
28 (a) A soldier or airman of the Arkansas National Guard may attend a
29 state-supported institution of higher education tuition-free if the soldier
30 or airman:
31 (1) Is an Arkansas resident or is eligible for in-state tuition
32 under ยง 6-60-205;
33 (2) Except as provided in subdivision (f)(3) of this section,
34 has completed initial active duty training;
35 (3) Except as provided in subsection (f) of this section, is in
36 good standing as an active soldier or airman of the Arkansas National Guard;
